doc.after: Singapore is a parliamentary republic with a Westminster system of unicameral parliamentary government representing constituencies The country s constitution establishes a representative democracy as the political system 33 Freedom House ranks Singapore as partly free in its Freedom in the World report 34 and The Economist ranks Singapore as a flawed democracy the second best rank of four in its Democracy Index 35
